"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 12, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ety1665702678389.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702678389.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ety1665702678389.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ety1665702678389\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines the function codes that are valid for this driver.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702678389__section_w2110ab1b5b1_w2111ab1b5_w2112ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449060e49\">Expected Input</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132158e1_d132159e1_d132160e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702678389__section_w2113ab1b5b3_w2114ab1b5_w2115ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449060e63\">Expected Output</h2>\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"ety1665702678389__parml_yzz_v5p_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">Flags1</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Manipulated using macros.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702678389__section_w2116ab1b5b5_w2117ab1b5_w2118ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449060e83\">Return Values</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"ety1665702678389__parml_cs1_bvp_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">USEC_SUCCESS</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">All initializations have successfully completed and the driver is ready to\n            continue.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">USEC_ERROR</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Driver initialization failed</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702678389__section_w2119ab1b5b7_w2120ab1b5_w2121ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449060e110\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132173e1_d132174e1_d132175e1\">Each security driver must supply information about the\n        functionality that it intends to provide by setting a number of flags in the supplied\n        structure. The flags indicate the function codes that are valid for the driver, and are\n        checked before the function is actually called. This prevents unnecessary calls to security\n        driver functions.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132176e1_d132177e1_d132178e1\">The driver should perform any initialization or memory\n        allocation it requires and use the member <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DrvArea</span> to pass information\n        between calls. The driver is responsible for releasing these resources.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132179e1_d132180e1_d132181e1\">If <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_ERROR</code> is returned, the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">USecDrv</code> structure is de-allocated. The driver must free its own allocated\n        resources before returning. The returned error message must be a fixed string, as its scope\n        must make it available to the caller.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132182e1_d132183e1_d132184e1\">For the C language, macros are provided for setting\n        and getting the the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Flags1</code> member of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USecDrv</span> driver\n        structure.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ety1665702678389__section_atn_gvp_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d449060e143\">SMTP Security Drivers</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ety1665702678389__p_d132188e1_d132189e1_d132190e1\">The parameters of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SetSecurity</span>\n        operation of the UPOPMAIL component are supplied in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code> and\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code> members as input to this function.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmx1665702774286.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Security Driver Macros</a><p>The USEC_DRVINFO function sets a number of bits in the Flags1 member of the supplied structure uSecDrv. In the C language, these must be set and read using macros.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527307\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527307\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USEC_DRVINFO Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 12, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determines the function codes that are valid for this driver. Expected Input Properties , Parameters Expected Output Flags1 Manipulated using macros. Return Values USEC_SUCCESS All initializations have successfully completed and the driver is ready to continue. USEC_ERROR Driver initialization failed Description Each security driver must supply information about the functionality that it intends to provide by setting a number of flags in the supplied structure. The flags indicate the function codes that are valid for the driver, and are checked before the function is actually called. This prevents unnecessary calls to security driver functions. The driver should perform any initialization or memory allocation it requires and use the member DrvArea to pass information between calls. The driver is responsible for releasing these resources. If USEC_ERROR is returned, the USecDrv structure is de-allocated. The driver must free its own allocated resources before returning. The returned error message must be a fixed string, as its scope must make it available to the caller. For the C language, macros are provided for setting and getting the the Flags1 member of the USecDrv driver structure. SMTP Security Drivers The parameters of the SetSecurity operation of the UPOPMAIL component are supplied in the Properties and Parameters members as input to this function. Related Links Security Driver Macros The USEC_DRVINFO function sets a number of bits in the Flags1 member of the supplied structure uSecDrv. In the C language, these must be set and read using macros. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}